<td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   /pet sit down</span><hr size=1> I've timed this a little bit, and it doesn't seem like it makes pets regenerate hit points faster.  Is that the general consensus, that there's no point in telling your pet to sit? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uzyphyr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zyphyr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 488<br> <font color=#333333>(8/18/02 12:19:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=647.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: /pet sit down</span><hr size=1> It has been known for a very long time that /pet sit down does nothing for pet regen (though there are a few clueless individuals out there who still claim otherwise). <p><DIV style="position:relative; width=80%; filter:glow(color=FFFF00)"><h4>Zyphyr Runnersbane</h4></div>
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=44185">Vending Machine and Disciple of Zomm</a><br>
Cult of the Ancient Wyrm<br>
Solusek Ro<br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ubaisblackfingers.showPublicProfile?language=EN>BaisBlackfingers</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 41<br> <font color=#333333>(8/19/02 1:18:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=647.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: /pet sit down</span><hr size=1> It helps pet regen by making the pet not wander past parked MoB's when you finish one of 2-3 and thus get smacked around, but other than that, no =P <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uvumberkin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vumberkin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#333333>(8/22/02 3:22:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=647.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: /pet sit down</span><hr size=1> Any thoughts on whether it might help them meditate?  Haha, it sounds dumb, but I've noticed that the 50+ fire pets cast spells like crazy when first summoned, and then resort to meleeing most of the time after a while.  Maybe it was just a dumb pet, but I was wondering if they have limited mana pools available to them, and if so, if sitting helps them recover that mana more quickly. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/urhionsligo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>rhionsligo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 948<br> <font color=#333333>(8/22/02 9:08:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=647.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.lehigh.edu/~dsf3/EQ/starofdavid.gif width=36 height=37></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: /pet sit down</span><hr size=1> pretty sure they do have mana pools...however all NPCs dont need to sit down to regenerate. all they require is to not be in combat to regenerate at their best rate. <p><img src="http://www.lehigh.edu/~dsf3/EQ/rhionsligo.jpg" align="center"><br>
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=106710">My Character Profile</a>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uzacatac.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zacatac</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 1103<br> <font color=#333333>(8/22/02 11:16:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=647.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: /pet sit down</span><hr size=1> Back when pets were aggro, I often used /pet sit down with the spell summon companion.<br>
<br>
/pet sit down<br>
<br>
I go move through the dungeon to another area and leave the pet behind because bad pathing or other reasons make having it follow me dangerous.<br>
<br>
Summon companion.  Pet is now at my side.<br>
<br>
If you told him /pet guard here, and summon him, he would run back to the spot you told him to guard if you didn't give him a new command. <p><DIV style="position:relative; width=80%; filter:glow(color=FF0000)"><a style="font-weight:bold; color:#FFFFFF; text-decoration: none" href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4796  target="new-window">Zacatac Soulwanderer</a></div>
